Github is the central repository which hosts the projects and save the changes that are made to the project.
In order to learn how github is helpful in maintaining a project let us create a new repository
How to create a new repository in github?
-> On the top right corner of the github home page there is a "+" symbol.
-> click on the + symbol you will get a few options in the dropdown
-> click on the "new repository" option
-> Give the name of the repository of you own
->then choose whether your project should be public or private
->you can also add readme file that have brief description about the repository
